<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8648> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8648" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 741, footnote 156" ;
	dprr:hasID 8648 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3293> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3293" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Gaul, where he founded Aquae Sextiae (Liv. Per. 61; Strabo 4.1.5; Vell. 1.15.4; Cassiod), and whence he returned to celebrate a triumph over the Ligurians, Vocontii and Salluvii (Act. Tr., Degrassi 82f., 560; see 124, Consuls, and 123, Promagistrates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3293 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3270> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3270" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in command against the Salluvii, whom he defeated (Liv. Per. 61). See 124, Consuls, and 122, Promagistrates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3270 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3245> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3245" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Eutropius has confused the name of Sextius with that of his successor Domitius, the Consul of 122, and has wrongly attributed to Cassius a share in the Gallic war and in the resulting triumph. See 122, Promagistrates; RE s. v. \"Domitius\" nos. 20 and 46." ;
	dprr:hasID 3245 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3244> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3244" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Vell. 1.15.4; Obseq. 31; Eutrop. 4.22; Chr. 354 (Longino et Calvino); Fast. Hyd. (Longino et Bulvino); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod. (C. Cassius Longinus et C. Sextius); and on Sextius, Diod. 34.23; Strabo 4.1.5; and on his name, Act. Tr. for 122. See Degrassi 126, 472f. Cassius may have founded Fabrateria to replace Fregellae (Vell. 1.15.4; see 125, Praetors). Sextius, along with his predecessor Fulvius, made war on the Ligurians, the Salluvii and the Vocontii (Diod. 34.23; Eutrop. 4.22;\n     see 123 and 122, Promagistrates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3244 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3224> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3224" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible dates for their praetorships under the Lex Villia. On Calvinus, see CIL 1\n     .2.801." ;
	dprr:hasID 3224 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10220> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10220" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Liguribus, Vocontieis, Salluveisque. MRR I.518, Itgenshorst no. 218, Rich no. 218." ;
	dprr:hasID 10220 .
